author: Kurtis Alexander
title: El Niño update: Most of California now forecast to be wet
text:
Photo: Scott Strazzante, The Chronicle Curtis Sims wlks on the new levy built near a creek behind his home in East Palo Alto, Calif., on Thursday, October 15, 2015. Sims' home was flooded during the 1997-98 El Nino. Curtis Sims wlks on the new levy built near a creek behind his home...
Drought-stricken California got a bit of good news Thursday when federal forecasters said parts of the state that need roof-pounding El Niño storms the most are likely to get them.
